=begin pod
=head1 Signals

=comment -----------------------------------------------------------------------
=head3 got-page-size

Emitted once for each page that gets rendered to the preview.

A handler for this signal should update the C<$context>
according to C<$page-setup> and set up a suitable cairo
context, using L<.set-cairo-context() in class PrintContext|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/PrintContext#set-cairo-context>.

=begin code
method handler (
  N-Object $context,
  N-Object $page-setup,
  Int :$_handle_id,
  N-GObject :$_native-object,
  Gnome::Gtk4::PrintOperationPreview :$_widget,
  *%user-options
)
=end code

=item $context; the current L<Gnome::Gtk4::PrintContext|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/PrintContext>.
=item $page-setup; the L<Gnome::Gtk4::PageSetup|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/PageSetup> for the current page.
=item $_handle_id; The registered event handler id.
=item $_native-object; The native object provided by the Raku object which registered this event. This is a native B<Gnome::Gtk4::PrintOperationPreview> object.
=item %user-options; A list of named arguments provided by L<.register-signal() in class Object|/content-docs/api2/reference/GObject/Object#register-signal>.

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for signal got-page-size

=end comment

